 prepare jar, place <b>500 g<b> water in mixing bowl. Place jar and lid upside down in the centre of the Varoma and steam <b><strong>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/strong>.<b>  Leave to drain - do not dry or touch the inside surfaces. Alternatively, thoroughly wash jar and lid in hot, soapy water. Rinse by pouring over boiling water. Prepare for filling, if needed, by placing on a clean tea towel in a roasting tin and heat in the oven at 100ËšC until required.","Store in the fridge for up to <b>3 months,<b> or freeze in cubes for up to <b>6 months.<b>","<b>1 heaped tsp<b> stock paste is roughly equivalent to <b>1 shop-bought<b> chicken stock cube (for <b>0.5 l).<b>","To make chicken stock, use <b>1 heaped tsp<b> per <b>500 g<b> water.","Adapt the stock paste recipe using the natural ingredients of your choice."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","45m","1"]}